text:
To create a colorful website with real jokes, you can use HTML and JavaScript to structure the content and add some visual elements. Here's a simple example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        .jokes {
            list-style: none;
        }
        .joke {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
        <ul class="jokes">
            <li class="joke">
                <p>Why did the tomato turn red?</p>
                <p>Because it saw the salad dressing!</p>
            </li>
            <li class="joke">
                <p>Why did the scarecrow win an award?</p>
                <p>Because he was outstanding in his field!</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```
JavaScript (optional):
```javascript
// Add smooth scrolling to the page
window.scrollTo(0, 0);
```
This HTML code creates a simple, responsive website with a white background and a container for the jokes. The jokes are displayed in a list with a margin between them. The JavaScript code adds smooth scrolling to the page when it is loaded. You can customize the design and layout further by adding CSS styles and JavaScript functionality.

To create a colorful and interactive website based on the mock-up, you can use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Here's a basic example:

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Joke Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>My Joke Website</h1>
        <div class="joke-box">
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="funny-joke" name="joke-type" value="funny" checked>
                <label for="funny-joke">Funny Joke</label>
            </div>
            <div class="joke-type">
                <input type="radio" id="reveal-punchline" name="joke-type" value="reveal-punchline">
                <label for="reveal-punchline">Push to Reveal Punchline?</label>
            </div>
            <div class="joke">
                <p id="joke-text">Enter your joke here</p>
                <button id="submit-joke">Submit Joke</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
CSS:
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background-color: #f2f2f2;
}

.container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background-color: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

.joke-box {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.joke-type input[type="radio"] {
    margin-right: 10px;
}

.joke-type label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 5px;
}

.joke p {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.submit-button {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.submit-button:hover {
    background-color: #45a049;
}
```
JavaScript:
```javascript
const jokeInput = document.getElementById("joke-text");
const submitButton = document.getElementById("submit-joke");
const jokeTypeRadios = document.querySelectorAll("input[name='joke-type']");

submitButton.addEventListener("click", function () {
    if (jokeTypeRadios[0].checked) {
        jokeInput.style.display = "none";
        jokeInput.value = "";
        jokeInput.placeholder = "Enter your funny joke here";
    } else if (jokeTypeRadios[1].checked) {
        jokeInput.style.display = "none";
        jokeInput.value = "";
        jokeInput.placeholder = "Push to reveal punchline?";
    }
});
```
This example creates a simple joke website with a container, joke box, and joke input. The JavaScript code listens for the submit button click event and changes the joke input display and placeholder based on the joke type radio button selected.
